    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It’s possible if you set `paginationLimitedTo` to a higher value in each index.\r\n\r\nHowever, it’s not ideal since it has a performance, and usually not necessary, since users rarely go beyond the first pages. \r\n\r\n> We recommend keeping the default value to guarantee excellent performance. Increasing the pagination limit will have a direct impact on the performance of search queries. A too high value will also make it very easy for anyone to retrieve (“scrape”) your entire dataset.\r\n\r\nsee https://www.algolia.com/doc/api-client/javascript/parameters/paginationLimitedTo/\r\n\r\nHave a great day!",
